  "summary": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 ships beacon scripts that exfiltrate host info via postinstall hook",
  "details": "On install, package.json declares a postinstall hook (\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\") that fires automatically when the package is installed. The package ships beacon34.js and beacon_linux.js which combine require('child_process'), require('https')/require('http'), os.hostname()/os.platform(), and process.env reads with outbound HTTP GET/POST/http.request calls — the canonical shape of a host-fingerprinting beacon that collects system identity and environment data and transmits it off-host at install time. The package has no legitimate library purpose visible in the shipped files; the entire on-install effect is the beacon execution.",
